Thinly slice the @scallions{2}(thinly sliced, keeping white and green parts separate). Peel the @ginger{1%thumb}(peeled) with a #spoon{} and then mince or grate along with the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Cut the @lime{1}(cut into wedges) into wedges. Thinly slice the @baby bok choy{2}(thinly sliced) leaves and stems. Coarsely chop the @mint{1%sprig}(coarsely chopped). Seed and mince the @jalapeño{1}(seeded and minced). Cut the @silken tofu{1%block} into 1/2-inch cubes.

Heat @vegetable oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a #pot{} over medium heat. Add the garlic, scallion whites, ginger, and as much jalapeño as you dare and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Add the @pho stock concentrate{1} and @water{4%cups}. Bring to a boil and then reduce to a simmer for ~{10%minutes}.

Add the tofu, 1/3 of the @rice noodles{1%pack}, and bok choy to the broth. Simmer until the noodles are tender, about ~{4%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Serve the pho in #bowls{} and top with mint, scallion greens, and a lime wedge.

> This classic Vietnamese soup will warm your belly this winter. Garlic, ginger, and mint create a fragrant broth, and bok choy adds a splash of color. Have your own chopsticks? Now's the time to use them to slurp up all those delicious rice noodles!